headline: Morgan Stanley sees a multi-year path to nearly $400B of Agentic Commerce
summary: Investing.com -- Morgan Stanley outlines a clear, multi-year route to what it describes as a nearly $400B agentic commerce market, grounded entirely in its latest AlphaWise consumer survey and internal forecasts.

headline: Could Ending a Major Legal Dispute Shift Morgan Stanley’s (MS) Risk Profile and Growth Strategy?
summary: Morgan Stanley recently resolved a long-running legal issue by accepting a €101 million fine from Dutch authorities for historical dividend tax evasion between 2007 and 2012, settling with both prosecutors and tax administrators. This resolution has removed a major legal overhang for the firm at a time when it continues to broaden business lines and innovate, such as through expansion into crypto services and wealth management growth initiatives.
